reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works, feels a little brittle
reviews.reviewText: I haven't had this long enough to report on its durability, but I am a little concerned about the clip that attaches to my GPS emergency beacon, as it feels a little cheap and brittle. It hasn't failed or anything, and it attached pretty easily, so I guess time will tell.As far as usefulness, it's great. I like that I can quickly detach it to check my map/location, and have it tethered to my shoulder strap. It attaches and detaches very easily, even with heavy winter gloves on. That alone makes it well worth the price. It's actually easier than using the clip/carabiner that came with the device.Overall, I would recommend this. It's an upgrade from the basic clip that my unit came with for sure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A nice accessory for my handheld.
reviews.reviewText: I have a spine mount for my Garmin eTrex30 that goes on my bicycle, but haven’t ever had a good way to carry it for hiking. Usually I just toss it in my backpack and check on it from time to time. This is a way better solution and I should not have waited so long to get a mount like this. It’s well built and solid. Nice knowing my gps is handy now.
